Question:
The surfaces in < image 2 > that can be obtained from the rectangular strip of paper shown in < image 1 > by gluing the arrows together are:

Options:
A: Only (a)
B: Only (b)
C: (a) and (b)
D: None
E: \\

message.content:
The strip in image 1 has both arrows pointing in the same direction along the width of the strip. Gluing the ends so that the arrows match requires no twist: we join the two ends with the same orientation. That produces an ordinary cylinder (a ring) as in image 2 (a).  

To get the twisted band (a Möbius strip) shown in image 2 (b), one end must be rotated 180° before gluing, which would reverse the arrow direction and thus does not match the arrows from image 1. So (b) cannot be obtained under the arrow-matching rule.

Answer:A
